TITLE: Page View Implementation
DESCRIPTION: Django view for handling dynamic pages from Directus collection.
SOURCE: https://github.com/directus/docs/blob/main/content/tutorials/1.getting-started/fetch-data-from-directus-with-django.md#2025-04-09_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: python
CODE:
```
from django.shortcuts import render
from django.http import JsonResponse
from .directus_integration import get_collection_items

def page_view(request, slug):
    pages = get_collection_items('pages')
    page = next((p for p in pages['data'] if p['slug'] == slug), None)
    if page:
        return render(request, 'page.html', {'page': page})
    else:
        return JsonResponse({'error': 'Page not found'}, status=404)
```

