TITLE: Implementing Weather Endpoint in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: Create an endpoint that fetches weather data from the Open-Meteo API based on provided longitude and latitude.
SOURCE: https://github.com/directus/docs/blob/main/content/tutorials/5.extensions/display-external-weather-api-data-in-custom-panels.md#2025-04-09_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
export default {
    id: 'weather',
    handler: (router) => {
        router.get('/', async (req, res) => {
            try {
                const response = await fetch(`https://api.open-meteo.com/v1/forecast?current_weather=true&${req._parsedUrl.query}`);

                if (response.ok) {
                    res.json(await response.json());
                } else {
                    res.status(response.status).send(response.statusText);
                }
            } catch(error) {
                res.status(500).send(error.message);
            }
        })
    }
}
```

